<subSubSection pageId="348" pageNumber="349" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="348" pageNumber="349">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="348" pageNumber="349">
The range of this eastern species extends from Cape Breton Island (Lindroth 1954c: 302) to eastern South Dakota (Kirk and Balsbaugh 1975: 17), south to east-central Louisiana (West Feliciana Parish, Igor M. Sokolov pers. comm. 2009), southwestern Mississippi (Drew A. Hildebrandt pers. comm. 2007), and northern Georgia (Fattig 1949: 17). The record from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Kansas”">&quot;Kansas&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Bousquet and Larochelle 1993: 134) needs confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
